<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.208058>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Periclimenaeus echinimanus sp. nov., male holotype, total view, lateral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/208058/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.208059>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Periclimenaeus echinimanus sp. nov., male holotype. A, rostrum, lateral. B, anterior carapace and appendages, dorsal. C, first abdominal segment, dorsal. D, sixth abdominal segment, telson and uropod, dorsal. E, left antenna, ventral. F, endopod of first pleopod. G, second pleopod, appendices interna and masculina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/208059/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.208060>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Periclimenaeus echinimanus sp. nov., male holotype. A, first pereiopod. B, same, chela. C, major second pereiopod, chela and carpus, medial. D, same, distal palm and fingers, medial. E, same, carpus to basis, lateral. F, minor second pereiopod, medial. G, same, distal palm and fingers, medial. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/208060/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.208061>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Periclimenaeus echinimanus sp. nov., male holotype. A, third pereiopod, lateral. B, same, dactylus and distal propodus, medial. C, fourth pereiopod, lateral. D, same, dactylus and distal propodus, lateral. E, fifth pereiopod, medial. F, same, dactylus and distal propodus, medial." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/208061/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.208062>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Periclimenaeus echinimanus sp. nov., ovigerous female allotype, mouthparts. A, right mandible. B, same, molar and incisor processes. C, same, incisor process. D, same, molar process, anterior view. E, left mandible. F, same, incisor process. G, same, molar process, anterior view. H, right maxillula. I, left maxillula. J, same, distal margin of upper lacinia. K, left maxilla. L, right maxilla, palp and endites. M, left first maxilliped. N, left second maxilliped. O, left third maxilliped, lateral. P, same, proximal segments, medial. Q, same, central part of exopod. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, E, H, I, K – P), 0.5 mm (B, D, F, G), 0.25 mm (C, J, Q)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/208062/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.208064>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Host sponges of Periclimenaeus echinimanus sp. nov. A – B, sponge (ii) from solid coral rock surface. C – D, sponge host (iii) overgrowing dead branches of Stylophora spp. coral. 10 mm (ABD), 5 mm (C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/208064/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

